Develop a C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file.

[The Start of Assistant A's Answer]
Here's a sample C++ program that does just that:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    ifstream file("input.txt"); // Open the input file
    string wordToSearch = "specific"; // The word to search for
    string line;
    int wordCount = 0;

    if (file.is_open()) {
        // Read the file line by line
        while (getline(file, line)) {
            size_t pos = 0;
            // Find the specific word in the line
            while ((pos = line.find(wordToSearch, pos)) != string::npos) {
                wordCount++; // Increment the word count
                pos += wordToSearch.length(); // Move the position to the end of the word
            }
        }
        file.close(); // Close the file
    } else {
        cout << "Unable to open file" << endl;
        return 1;
    }

    cout << "The word \"" << wordToSearch << "\" appears " << wordCount << " times in the file." << endl;

    return 0;
}
```

This program opens a file called "input.txt" and reads it line by line, searching for occurrences of the word "specific" in each line. It then counts the total number of occurrences and prints the result. You can replace "input.txt" with the desired file name and "specific" with the word you want to search for.
